69th Legislature 2025 HB 456
AN ACT EXPANDING THE BEST BEGINNINGS CHILD CARE SCHOLARSHIP PROGRAM TO PROVIDE
SCHOLARSHIPS TO CHILD-CARE WORKERS EMPLOYED BY A LICENSED DAY-CARE CENTER OR
REGISTERED FAMILY OR GROUP DAY-CARE HOME; PROVIDING AN APPROPRIATION; AMENDING
SECTIONS 52-2-714 AND 52-2-715, MCA; AND PROVIDING AN EFFECTIVE DATE.
BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF MONTANA:
Section 1. Section 52-2-714, MCA, is amended to read:
"52-2-714. Best beginnings child care scholarship program. There is a best beginnings child care
scholarship program administered by the department. The program is established to provide scholarships to
qualified low-income families and eligible child-care workers employed at a licensed day-care center or
registered family or group day-care home whose child received care provided by a licensed or registered child
care child-care provider or day-care facility."
Section 2. Section 52-2-715, MCA, is amended to read:
"52-2-715. Family income eligibility -- child-care worker eligibility -- requirements. (1) In Except
as provided in subsection (2), in determining income eligibility for qualified low-income families for the best
beginnings child care scholarship program, the department shall:
(1)(a) set a qualifying income threshold at no less than 185% of the federal poverty level for each
family size; and
(2)(b) set a maximum qualifying income level that is no higher than that allowed by the federal child
care and development block grant.
(2) A child-care worker is eligible for the best beginnings child care scholarship program if the
worker:
