(a) is employed at a licensed day-care center or registered family or group day-care home for at
least the minimum number of hours required as established by the department pursuant to 45 CFR 98.16(g) ;
and
(b) has a household income that is less than two times the state median income."
Section 3. Appropriation. There is appropriated $5.5 million from the general fund to the department
of public health and human services for each year of the biennium beginning July 1, 2025, for the purposes of
providing best beginnings child care scholarships to eligible child-care workers as provided in [section 1].
Section 4. Effective date. [This act] is effective July 1, 2025.
